OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772301852
OL,3,CHospice turning dying patients away
OL,4,Cbecause it can't afford to keep beds
OL,5,Copen
OL,7,FFor those lucky enough to receive care
OL,8,Fit is the kind of place many people
OL,9,Fwould probably hope to spend their
OL,10,Fdays.
OL,12,FMaggie Mobey has cancer and
OL,13,FParkinson's disease and is currently
OL,14,Fbeing looked after at Prospect Hospice
OL,15,Fin Wroughton.
OL,17,FMrs Mobey said: "It's really lovely.
OL,18,FIt's all nice and quiet. No machines
OL,19,Fbuzzing and popping. Not so many
OL,20,Ftrolleys going round and round. Really
OL,21,Fpeaceful."
OL,26,@yD@QOU}D@JO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772301852
OL,3,CHospice turning dying patients away
OL,4,Cbecause it can't afford to keep beds
OL,5,Copen
OL,7,FMrs Mobey was diagnosed at the Great
OL,8,FWestern Hospital in Swindon, but she
OL,9,Fhad to wait two weeks there for her
OL,10,Fplace at Prospect. And as the family
OL,11,Fdiscovered, a lack of hospice beds
OL,12,Fmeans a lack of hospital beds.
OL,14,FHer husband Vincent Mobey said:
OL,15,F"People are in hospital at the moment
OL,16,Fthat dearly need to go to a hospice.
OL,17,FBut there's no bed for them. So they
OL,18,Fstay in hospital.
OL,26,@wD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772301852
OL,3,CHospice turning dying patients away
OL,4,Cbecause it can't afford to keep beds
OL,5,Copen
OL,7,F"They're blocking a bed in the
OL,8,Fhospital. When Maggie went to hospital
OL,9,Fshe was in a corridor on a bed because
OL,10,Fthere was nowhere for her to go."
OL,12,FHospice leaders say the problems are
OL,13,Fbecoming more common. Half of the
OL,14,Ftwelve specialist beds at Prospect are
OL,15,Fclosed. In a typical week, they say
OL,16,Fsix or seven dying patients are turned
OL,17,Faway.
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@aO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772301852
OL,3,CHospice turning dying patients away
OL,4,Cbecause it can't afford to keep beds
OL,5,Copen
OL,7,FJeremy Lune, CEO of Prospect Hospice
OL,8,Fsaid: "We've currently got 6 beds open
OL,9,Fdelivering our brilliant specialist
OL,10,Fcare. There is a need in our
OL,11,Fcommunity, which is really clearly
OL,12,Fdocumented, for 12 of those beds to be
OL,13,Fopen.
OL,15,F"At the moment, we can't afford to,
OL,16,Fand that means people who should be
OL,17,Fwith us are spending their time in
OL,18,Fhospital corridors, or in the wrong
OL,19,Fbeds in hospitals."
OL,26,@pD@GOUwD@AOU{D@SO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772301852
OL,3,CHospice turning dying patients away
OL,4,Cbecause it can't afford to keep beds
OL,5,Copen
OL,7,FIn England, hospices are charities. On
OL,8,Faverage, around thirty per cent of
OL,9,Ftheir funding comes from the NHS, the
OL,10,Frest from fundraising.
OL,12,FAt Prospect Hospice, government
OL,13,Ffunding makes up just eighteen per
OL,14,Fcent of its income. The rest comes
OL,15,Ffrom charity shops, fundraising events
OL,16,Fand legacies.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772301852
OL,3,CHospice turning dying patients away
OL,4,Cbecause it can't afford to keep beds
OL,5,Copen
OL,7,FA lack of money makes the hospice more
OL,8,Fexpensive to run. With only six beds
OL,9,Fopen, the hospice says costs rise to
OL,10,Faround #1,500 per patient, per night,
OL,11,Fcompared to just #1,100 if all twelve
OL,12,Fbeds were operating.
OL,14,FThe government says it has provided
OL,15,F#125 million for hospices, calling it
OL,16,Fthe biggest investment in a
OL,17,Fgeneration. But that money was a one-
OL,18,Foff, not a system change.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772301852
OL,3,CHospice turning dying patients away
OL,4,Cbecause it can't afford to keep beds
OL,5,Copen
OL,7,FJeremy Lune added: "That money was
OL,8,Fcapital funding. It covered the fact
OL,9,Fthat our roof was partially ripped off
OL,10,Fduring Storm Claudia and our central
OL,11,Fheating packed up.
OL,13,F"It doesn't cover, for any of the
OL,14,Fhospices, the need to increase our
OL,15,Fstaffing levels to meet the needs of
OL,16,Fthe population. We need a funding
OL,17,Fmodel that reflects that. The number
OL,18,Fof people that are living longer, and
OL,19,Fneeding our services, is increasing."
OL,26,@oD@TOUuD@AOU{D@eO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/8
